# S05: Work Control Orchestrator

## Objective
Evolve `apps/work-control` from a Totem reader into a chat-driven AI work
orchestrator. Ship the full spine **end-to-end with MOCK agents**:

```
chats â†’ chat â†’ epics â†’ epic (board) â†’ tasks â†’ task
```

A ROOT agent watches the chat + project context and proposes an editable
**Epics** list (right column). Accepting an epic makes PLANNER decompose it into
a board of tasks AND **write `.ptl`/`.pd` files at `gate: LOCKED`** into the
Totem instance. A human then **opens the gate**; only then may a (mock) agent run
a task `todo â†’ in_progress â†’ done`, streamed live over a Nitro WebSocket.

## Foundation decisions (frozen â€” see S05-INVARIANTS.md)
- Agent runtime: **MOCK** (deterministic) this sprint; real LLM deferred to S06.
- Realtime: **Nitro WebSocket (crossws)** â€” local-first, no Supabase realtime.
- Totem link: **write-back** â€” app generates real `.ptl`/`.pd` at `gate: LOCKED`; human opens.
- Persistence: **Supabase** datasource (multi-user), via `CORE_DATASOURCE_*`.
- Agent-role taxonomy: **organization layer** (`app.config.ts` `agents` block).

